<p>The following controller has <strong>numberOfRowsInSection:</strong> ofUITableViewDataSource.</p>  <pre><code>class CityList: UIViewController,UITableViewDataSource,UITableViewDelegate {    weak var cityListArray:NSMutableArray? = nil  func tableView(tableView: UITableView, numberOfRowsInSection section: Int) -&gt; Int { return self.cityListArray?.count } } </code></pre>  <p><code>return self.cityListArray?.count</code> shows Value of optional type int? not unwrapped did you mean to use '!' or "?"</p>  <p>How can I use ternary operator here, to return 0 if the array was empty?</p>  <p>Objective-C had default value returned 0, if the object is nil.</p>